NAME: Lia Hakso
REVIEW:
Menurut saya ini kafe yang potensial untuk berkembang. Penataan ruangnya menarik dengan racikan kopi yang unik. Ruangan yang tidak terlalu luas ini juga membuat pengunjung nyaman ngobrol santai dengan pemilik sekaligus baristanya.
Golden macchiato di sini unik sekali rasanya. Kandungan kunyitnya mengurangi pahitnya kopi sekaligus memperkaya rasa.
Sebaiknya sih memaksimalkan aset digital seperti instagram atau youtube. Minimal untuk memperkenalkan produk kepada masyarakat.

NAME: Liow Mei Fong
REVIEW:
Get your Jawa here. Come here for local coffee from all over Jawa, whether you like it to be dripped, Machined.

More importantly the golden macchiato coffee made with Tumeric.

NAME: Tiwie Pidada
REVIEW: Best coffee in town so far. Very cozy place, such a hidden gem in the middle of taman sari's crowd. Lucky enough to meet the friendly owner/barista :) highly recommended place!

NAME: Axel Philip
REVIEW: Cosy and comfortable place to refresh after a hot walk in Jogja. The owner is very friendly and drinks taste good (I recommend the sparkling orange) !

NAME: Fabiano D'Amico
REVIEW: Good Espresso and juice in a touristic place! Kind and warm staff. If you want to stop for a quick drink I recommend to come here!

NAME: Justyna Sienkiewicz
REVIEW: Iced coffee kraton served by the friendly owner/barista is the way to stay cool while sightseeing the main landmarks of the old town of Jogja.

NAME: 伊藤賢治
REVIEW:
Kafe yang bagus untuk bersantai.
Saya juga merasakan komitmen terhadap menu.
Vanilla latte, tidak terlalu manis dan enak! !

NAME: Aimee Mullins
REVIEW: Cute friendly cafe great service with a smile

NAME: Dominic Potter
REVIEW: Naris the Barista makes one of the best coffees in the city. He has his own blends made from locally produced coffee beans. Great place to relax and enjoy a coffee or tea.

NAME: Brilian Aulia
REVIEW: Javanese oriental coffe beans and Snacks.

NAME: Carlos García
REVIEW: Tempat yang tenang untuk beristirahat dari hiruk pikuk dan panasnya kota. Kopi yang enak.

NAME: Washo Bugbear
REVIEW: Found this place by accident as we left Taman Sari. Lovely little coffee shop, cold drinks too. Very friendly staff and all immaculately clean. Best so far in Jogja.

NAME: pazzoll
REVIEW: Excellent coffee and Aji the owner is a great host. Ask him anything you want about Javanese coffee - he will serve it to you with pride.

NAME: Hendrik Damerow
REVIEW: Extraordinary coffee and iced Thai tea. Really fair prices considering the location. Nice interior, friendly staff !

NAME: John Sones
REVIEW: Best in the area, atmosphere, class, clean, excellent coffee and drinks
